OL,3,GCentral, Tayside & Fife
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA frosty, dry and sunny start
OL,6,Fto the day will be followed by
OL,7,Fbuilding cloud during the morning and
OL,8,Fa few outbreaks of rain spreading
OL,9,Fnorth towards the evening.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FCloudy with some patchy light
OL,12,Frain through the evening. Staying
OL,13,Fcloudy overnight with some heavier
OL,14,Fbursts of rain developing towards
OL,15,Fmorning.
OL,16,
OL,17,CWednesday:FLargely cloudy as bands of
OL,18,Frain push northeast in the morning.
OL,19,FTurning showery later, these showers
OL,20,Fheavy and thundery at times.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
